<i>Posted by Wildize Darkart on 10-26-2001 07:40 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Clown.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p>I've been spending quite a bit of time here trying to get this, and finally have a good approach, although no spell yet <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Battle Master Ska'Tu spawns inbetween the waterfall and the Grave Master spawn point along the path - I have only seen him in one place, but I think it can be any of the skelly spawn points. My regular group can hold this area, but I would not recommend it without a sold 55+ group. We cleared the area and then set up at the Grave Master spawn point - there are no adds from beyond there, and you can time the pops if you need to. I also found the pathing is easier to deal with from there. The trick to pulling in here is babysitting the mobs - especially the skellies. I walk up pretty close to them, get agro (spell or smacking them or whatever), then babysit them back to the group - this overrides the nasty pathing in there, and by doing this I can single and double the whole area. If you let the two skellies by the Grave Master path on their own when initially breaking, they will bring 4 for sure so be careful if your group can't handle that (we did it for fun last night muahaha).<br />
<br />
They bad news is the only drop I've seen so far is the Pally sword <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="">. I will be trying more this weekend. The Grave Master drops a reasonable pal/sk/clr no drop hammer though as a bonus - 16/22 1hb <insert some small stats here> and Effect: Expel Undead - not bad anyway, and fun to play with in there on the skellies!<br />
<br />
Btw, the exp is pretty good there in my opinion - I got 2 blue in 59 last night in about 3 hours.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
__________________<br>
