<i>Posted by Ronak on 01-14-2002 10:51 AM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Mad_As_Hell.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p>We hunted this area 4 nights with our regular group:<br />
60SK, 60CLR, 60WAR, 58 ROG, 58 ENC, 57 DRU<br />
<br />
Pretty good exp, but it gets rather dull. Pathing is a joke. Skeles <br />
are unable to path properly onto the path, sarnaks are unable <br />
to path properly off the path. After trying the babysitting method<br />
and trying the train yourself method...We found that not pulling<br />
at all was the best method. Simply move around the area instead<br />
of sitting and pulling to one spot, much easier. From bridge, we<br />
go off the path and fight the first skeles at once, then back to<br />
path for 2 sarnaks, then back off path for more skeles, etc...<br />
Repeat as respawn happens. Fairly easy, and constantly moving<br />
helps to break up the boredom a bit.<br />
<br />
We got several nice items down here (we call this area crypt), but<br />
no shroud of undeath. Eight or so BM kills, no spell. I loathe the<br />
idea of going back here, but I still want this damn spell...<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
__________________<br>
Ronak <br />
Gravelord of Machin Shin<br />
Xegony</font></p>
